// This text will be stored with each diagram;  use it for notes.


It is assumed that the opening and closing of the valve are continuous processes.
This means that it is imposssible to a receive a *valveClosed* event if the valve is opening 
nor is it possible to receive a *valveOpened * event if the valve is closing.

If the valve were to close in the middle of equalizing the levels across the gate,
this would halt the normal operation. Somewhat like being stuck in an elevator</help_text>
